<br>
Tell me about heh.  There are a few places where taunt seems to be purposely toned down.  Haven't run my little test in Cazic Thule again since the supposed change to the tuant skill there, but from what hunts I've had there the last time it sure seems like it's only partially working.<br>
<br>
Test being, get an invis, walk up to a mob, and tuant it.  You'll most likely have to tuant repeatedly since the skill fails a lot (just a percentage chance roll to see whether you taunted or didn't... fail the roll and nothing happens at all, win the roll and you're on the aggro list and the mob attacks you).<br>
<br>
When I did this in CT, before the tuant skill was fixed there, out of 30 tuant button presses that lizard never aggroed on me.  He just stood there calmly at his spawn location the entire time, didn't even know I was there because of invis.  Verdict?  Tuant was completely disabled in that zone at the time I did that.  Could press the key till you were blue in the face (which is what I basically did) and it would never successfully win the roll.<br>
<br>
Most mobs everywhere that I've done this to took 1 to 5 presses to aggro them.  Averaging around 2 presses.  It wouldn't suprise me one bit if the number of presses in ME, and a few other places, were a bit higher.<br>
<br>
I haven't run the test in the Plane of Sky yet, but would like to the next time I'm there.  Everytime that I've been there I could have sworn the tuant skill did nothing to the 51+ mobs there also (which would make sense, since it's an old world engine containing mobs that are 51+... just like Cazic was before they had to change it).  The level 50 thunder spirits were the only mobs that I can remember turning to me with consistancy upon most taunt presses.  The other mobs are all 51+. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubinnamar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Binnamar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 136<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/1/02 1:36:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4051.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I can taunt!</span><hr size=1> Let the 2 mage pets tank. Send them in one at a time wait a second and just run in there and bash the mob. The pets will (maybe not anymore after some patches) hold agro and you won't get hit. Works like a charm, as long as the mage/cleric can keep the pets healed. <p>Binnamar- 51 dwarven warrior<BR>
